entries.meaning: A small fern, Botrychium lunaria (lesser moonwort); later, any member of the genus. [from 15th c.]
examples: Moonwort is an herb which they say will open locks, and unshoe such horses as tread upon it.

entries.meaning: (now US, UK regional) Lunaria annua (greater moonwort); also known as Honesty and Actual Honesty. [from 16th c.]
